post_text:
Superintendent Kirbyâ€™s statement on Issue 26:

â€œOf course, I am disappointed in the levy results. This is an incredibly tough time for our community for many reasons. Itâ€™s unfortunate that because of the way our state funds EdChoice vouchers, our school district is left financially damaged. We are already in the process of making staffing and operational budget cuts to the tune of $2.5 million, and even more will likely be on the horizon. We will continue our advocacy work in ensuring that the state funds EdChoice vouchers directly instead of deducting the funds from public school districts. Itâ€™s an unsustainable funding model and must be changed.â€

Greater Cleveland Food Bank
March 24 at 12:30 PM Â·

It's Drive-Thru Distribution Day! We will be distributing shelf-stable emergency boxes of food anyone in need TODAY from 2 pm to 5 pm at the Food Bank! This will be a drive-thru process designed with your welfare, health, and safety at the forefront of our service to you. We are requiring for everyone to clear the trunks of their vehicles as we will be loading food into trunks. For safety reasons, we cannot enter a vehicle to load food. If you have any questions, please reach out at 216.738.2067.

post_text:
A Holiday Message from Superintendent Kirby:

Dear CH-UH Community,

I want to take a moment to wish you and your loved ones the happiest of holidays. No matter how, where, or what you are celebrating this time of year, I hope the joy and peace of the season find you and remind you of all the blessings in your lives. I look forward to reconnecting with you in the new year.

Sincerely,
Liz Kirby, CH-UH City Schools Superintendent
